Introduction

Ferry Blue is a six-member girl group formed by the K-Pop Music Production department at Paekche Institute of Arts and is currently under D Ocean Music. They made their debut on September 6, 2021, with the single "Call My Name". The group consists of the members Dozin, Xiho, Hyeyoung, Seul, Seona, and Hyunji.

In 2022, it was announced that Yeji would be leaving the group. Ferry Blue continued as a six-member group.
